title: Elimination Chamber: Bray Wyatt wins to become new WWE champion
text:
Bray Wyatt as the new WWE champion. Pic Courtesy/ WWE 
Becky Lynch vs. Mickie James 
Micke James returned to a main WWE main event after 7 years and looked to do away with ring rust. For most of the match, Mickey James began to target Becky Lynch's arm for most of the match. However, Becky managed to make a comeback and pin Mickey James for the win.
Apollo Crews and Kalisto vs. Dolph Ziggler 
As Kalisto entered, Dolph Ziggler attacked him. Apollo Crews and Ziggler began the match. Kalisto joined in as the two over powered Ziggler. Crews then pinned Ziggler after hitting him with the spin out powerbomb. After the match, Ziggler attacked both with a chair and targetted Crews' ankle.
Nikki Bella vs. Natalya 
After major trash talking, the two began to fight it out. They took the match outside the ring and gradually it resulted in a double count-out. They began to brawl even after the match ended.
Randy Orton vs. Luke Harper 
Orton and Harper went back and forth with both WWE wrestlers dominating off and on. Randy Orton then hit the RKO on Luke Harper for the win.
The Tag Team Turmoil match for the SmackDown Tag team titles 
Breezango and Rhyno and Slater began the match. Rhyno then hit the Gore on Fandango to pin him. Heath Slater then hit the DDT on English to pin him. American Alpha and The Usos then began fighting. Chad Gable then pinned Jey Uso to eliminate them. After that, the Usos attacked American Alpha. However, AA made a comeback and defeated Ascension to retain the WWE SmackDown tag team titles.
Alexa Bliss vs Naomi for the SmackDown Women's title

Pic Courtesy/ YouTube 
Alexa initially threw gum on Naomi's face mocking her. During the match Alexa tried to pin Naomi with her feet on the ropes, but the referee saw it. Naomi showcased immense skill with brilliant moves and then hit the split legged moonsault to pin Alexa Bliss and become the new WWE SmackDown women's champion.
John Cena vs. Bray Wyatt vs. AJ Styles vs. The Miz vs. Dean Ambrose vs. Baron Corbin for the WWE championship 
16-time champion John Cena was defending his WWE title and began the match with AJ Styles and had a few near falls. The first entrant was Dean Ambrose who turned things up a notch. Ambrose hit a diving elbow from the top of the pod to Cena. John Cena then hit the double german suplex on Styles and Dean Ambrose. Bray Wyatt was the next wrestler to enter and hit AJ Styles into the chamber wall. Baron Corbin nedt entered the Elimination Chamber and began hitting End of Days on his opponents. As the Miz had his turn to enter he stuck in the pod. Corbin stared at the Miz and this led Ambrose to pin Corbin. Baron Corbin then attacked Ambrose and threw him straight into the pod glass. He then hit End of Days on Ambrose and left. The Miz then entered and immediately pinned Ambrose. John Cena t hen hit the Attitude Adjustment on Miz to pin him. AJK Styles and Bray Wyatt then attacked John Cena. AJ Styles and John Cena, both hit each other with their signature moves and kicked out of them respectively. Bray Wyatt then hit John Cena with Sistwer Abigail to pin him. As AJ Styles went to hit the Phenomenal Forearm, Bray Wyatt countered it with sister Abigail to pin Styles and become the new WWE champion.
